@startuml
title Serialized node page layout

skinparam rectangle {
  RoundCorner 0
}

rectangle "Node page buffer" as page {
  rectangle "Header\n1 byte: isLeaf\n2 bytes: item count" as header
  rectangle "Left-growing directory\nFor each item:\n- child page id if internal\n- 2 byte item offset\nLast child page id for internal nodes" as directory
  rectangle "Unused space" as gap
  rectangle "Right-growing cells\nFor each item:\n- 1 byte key length\n- key bytes\n- 1 byte value length\n- value bytes" as cells
}

header -right- directory
directory -right- gap
gap -right- cells

directory --> cells : offsets point to cells

note bottom
serialize writes metadata from the left side of the page and variable-size key/value
cells from the right side. deserialize follows offsets to rebuild Node.items and
Node.childNodes.
end note

@enduml
